[SN]TITLE[SN]
European Champions Cup: Ulster start with Bordeaux trip

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Ulster will begin their European Champions Cup Pool 5 campaign against Bordeaux in France on 16 October.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It's followed by Kingspan Stadium clashes with Exeter six days later and Clermont Avergne on 10 December.
The return game against Clermont Avergne in France is on 18 December before a 13/14/15 January encounter with Exeter at Sandy Park Stadium.
Ulster, who won the competition in 1999, complete their pool games at home against Bordeaux on 20/22/22 January.
The Belfast side met French club Clermont in the 2011/12 competition with Ulster winning at Ravenhill before losing the return game.
Leinster open their Pool 4 fixtures against Castres at the RDS on 15 October and on the same day Connacht go up against four-time winners Toulouse at the Sportsground.
Racing 92 are first up for Munster in Pool 1 with the match at Stade Yves-Du-Manoir on 16 October.
